  "text": "In accordance with the approximate procedure for extraction of crack width, we first perform skeltonization over the binary detection results at time T1, T2, and T3. Figures 14(d)-14 (f) illustrate the centerlines of these multitemporal cracks. By solving [CITATION_1] for the SDFs and conducting Boolean operations to extract distance values at the centerlines, one obtains the approximate widths along cracks, denoted by w T1 (x, y), w T2 (x, y), and w T3 (x, y). Table 2 summarizes the statistics of these crack widths. Since it is difficult to plot extracted crack widths along the crack in a 2D domain, for width values in w(x, y), we plot the pairs (x, max y [w(x, y)]), that is, the xcoordinate versus the maximum width in y direction given x. These plots are shown in Figures 15(a)-15(c) .",
